      <hr><a name="skip_menu"></a><h1>007 - Notated Music (R)</h1>
      <hr>
      <div class="formatname">MARC 21 Bibliographic - Full</div>
      <div class="datename">October 2000</div>
      <hr><strong>Indicators and Subfield Codes</strong><div class="description">Field has no indicators or subfield codes; the data elements are positionally
                  defined.
      </div>
      <table width="100%">
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td width="45%"><strong>Character Positions</strong><br>
              <strong>00 - Category of material </strong><br>
              q - Notated music <br><br>
			
              <strong>01 - Specific material designation </strong><br>
           u - Unspecified <br>| - No attempt to code</td>
            <td width="45%">&nbsp;</td>
         </tr>
   </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>When field 007/00 contains code q, it contains special coded information that identifies
                     the item physically as a <strong>notated music</strong>.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> CHARACTER POSITIONS
      </h4>
      <div class="characterposition"><strong>00 - Category of material  </strong><div class="charactervalue"><strong>q - Notated music</strong> <div class="description">One-character alphabetic code that indicates the category of material to which
                                    the item belongs is <strong>notated music</strong>, which is defined as
                                    graphic, non-realized representations of musical works, both in printed and
                                    digitized manifestations. It includes musical scores and/or parts, diagrammatic
                                    representations, tablature, instructions for chance compositions, pictures or
                                    paintings intended as musical compositions, square note notation, klavarskribo,
                                    chant notation, neumes, braille, and other ways of representing the four
                                    components of musical sound: pitch, duration, timbre, and loudness. Notated
                                    music is often the means for communicating to the performer(s) how the musical
                                    work notated therein is to be realized in sound. A fill character (|) is not
                                    allowed in this position.
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <div class="characterposition"><strong>01 - Specific material designation  </strong><div class="description">Special class of textual material to which an item belongs.</div>
         <div class="charactervalue"><strong>u - Unspecified</strong> <div class="description">Special material designation for the notated music is not specified.</div>
         </div>
         <div class="charactervalue"><strong>| - No attempt to code</strong> </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span>EXAMPLE
      </h4>
      <div class="example">
